==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Continental drive
<hw>Con`ti*nen"tal drive</hw>. <fld>(Automobiles)</fld> <def>A
transmission arrangement in which the longitudinal crank shaft drives
the rear wheels through a clutch, change-speed gear, countershaft, and
two parallel side chains, in order.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Continental glacier</ent>⟦br⟧
